the simpler regression-imputation logic:
\enumerate{
\item Use the reduced model to impute \verb{E\{Y(d, M(d)) | C\}} and
\verb{E\{Y(dstar, M(dstar)) | C\}}.
\item Use the full model to predict \code{Y} under \code{D = d} while leaving the
observed mediators unchanged.
\item Regress those predictions on the reduced-model regressors to recover
\verb{E\{Y(d, M(dstar)) | C\}}.
\item Average the three potential-outcome means and take contrasts to obtain the
total effect, natural direct effect, and natural indirect effect.
